The paper deals with person re-identification, which is a computer vision problem, and specifically focuses on extracting semantically aligned part-level features from pedestrian images. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel method for multi-task learning, which involves optimizing the main task and auxiliary task for each body part, and using coarse priors of body part locations in the training stage. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions experiments on large-scale ReID databases, which suggests that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the problem of body part misalignment, which suggests that it may also belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category, as this is a common problem in biometric authentication systems.
